	<text>
		<body>
				<p rend="align(center)"><placeName>Boston</placeName> <date>Oct&#58; 23&#47;623</date></p>
				<p>Rev &#38; Dr Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Yours duly recd and have to inform you that <persName>Mr Spier</persName><lb/> gave the same answer as before&#58; &#8220;<persName>Philip</persName> has recd <hi rend="underline">none</hi>&#8221; <date>Sunday</date> I think<lb/> in the first meeting of the School before whom you claim will be presented&#44;<lb/> and as soon I will receive it I will forward it.</p>
				<p>In regard to the Church they intend purchasing I can only say that there<lb/> is no earthly possibility to do anything but making the entrance at <add>Hebrew</add><lb/> where it is now&#44; and the <add>Hebrew</add> either direct <hi rend="underline">North East</hi> or <hi rend="underline">North West</hi><lb/> the latter is the most probable side&#59; as for Reformers I do not care&#44;<lb/> I only care for the fanatics <add>Hebrew</add>...I believe the Hamburger<lb/> Synag. at <placeName>London</placeName> is neither placed <add>Hebrew</add> and believe it to be on<lb/> the North East&#44; I am not sure&#59; as I stated I am lacking<lb/> <add>&#63;</add> books <add>Hebrew</add> but I would say if you would discuss<lb/> the matter with some conversant in our Laws&#44; or having the required<lb/> books&#44; you would perceive that I am right to authorize the<lb/> Trustees&#44; under the existing circumstances to do it.  <persName>Mr Ettinger</persName>&#44;<lb/> <persName>Mr Pape</persName> Old <persName>Mr Heilprin</persName> <add>Hebrew</add> are able to decide the<lb/> matter&#44; they will find no difficulty whatever.  I have ordered<lb/> some books from <placeName>Europe</placeName> and will soon be out of my troubles</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">You will confer a great favor on me to attend to it at<lb/> your earliest convenience.  If purchased no messenger<lb/> or <add>Hebrew</add> you will officiate <add>Hebrew</add>.  I will look for that.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">The <sic>are</sic> resolutions passed touching myself &#38; Son shall<lb/> I send them to you or to the <add>Hebrew</add>&#63;  There are some notes of private<lb/> individuals which mys be written over&#44; send me word how to do</p>
			<p rend="indent(10)">Yours Truly</p>
			<p rend="indent(11)"><persName role="author">Simon le Noot</persName></p>
		</body>
